Package com.steelypip.powerups.jinxml

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Attribute
    Attributes represent a (key, value) pair.
    Attribute.Iterable
    The Attribute.Iterable class implements the main way to iterate over the attributes of an element and is returned from Element.attributes().
    Builder  
    Element  
    EventHandler
    This is the basic interface for incremental processing of an Element, especially construction.
    Member
    Members represent a (selector, element) pair.
    Member.Iterable
    The Member.Iterable class implements the main way to iterate over the members of an element and is returned from Element.members().
    PushParser
    A PushParser is a wrapper around a Reader.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Event
    As a push-parser scans an input stream, it emits a series of Events.
    Event.AttributeEvent
    This event corresponds to a key-value pair.
    Event.BooleanEvent
    This event corresponds to a boolean.
    Event.EndArrayEvent
    This event corresponds to the end of an array.
    Event.EndObjectEvent
    This event corresponds to the end of an object.
    Event.EndTagEvent
    This event corresponds to an end-tag.
    Event.FloatEvent
    This event corresponds to a float (not a int).
    Event.IntEvent
    This event corresponds to an int (not a float).
    Event.LiteralConstantEvent  
    Event.NullEvent
    This event corresponds to a null.
    Event.StartArrayEvent
    This event corresponds to the start of an array.
    Event.StartObjectEvent
    This event corresponds to the start of an object.
    Event.StartTagEvent
    This event corresponds to a start-tag, including the tag name and the name of the selector that links it to the parent.
    Event.StringEvent
    This event corresponds to a string.
